      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a driver-spec example featuring the 3.6L flat-six engine with VarioCam Plus. This unit delivers a linear power band through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including a ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal. The suspension has been enhanced with Bilstein B8 dampers and M030-spec sway bars for superior lateral stability. While the Arctic Silver finish shows minor road-going patina, the mechanicals are stout, featuring a dry undercarriage and a rev-happy throttle response. A technically sound 911 for the purist seeking visceral feedback.",
